SOURCE_NAME);\\n                try (InputStream stream = scanner.open()) {\\n                    assertThat(new String(stream.readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8)).isEqualTo(RESOURCE_CONTENT);\\n                }\\n                assertThat(scanner.hasNext()).isFalse();\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class SingleResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        private final String resourceName;\\n        private final URL resourceUrl;\\n\\n        private SingleResourceClassLoader(String resourceName, URL resourceUrl) {\\n            super(null);\\n            this.resourceName = resourceName;\\n            this.resourceUrl = resourceUrl;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Enumeration<URL> getResources(String name) throws IOException {\\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\\n                return Collections.enumeration(List.of(resourceUrl));\\n            }\\n            return Collections.emptyEnumeration();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-06T19-28-03-397911Z.log:3265:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying resource finding**\\n\\nI’m working with VfsResourceFinder, which only returns the name of the child with child.getName. For files, I can use `isLeaf` to check if it’s a file. When dealing with package directories, calling `getChildren` with recursive set to false will provide the immediate children. This way, I can efficiently gather the necessary information without going deeper into the directory structure.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_013668d52bbbe33c016a24747e30d48195a6093125e322125e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJHSV4MtEEVlFjxUOGvF72CGO5VQGdJUmaCR6kR8AVIBz8Tcw1I3kog9hmKGnBkvvCL25TdS8fmyWhIEGtVvyJ_S