{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_41","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7778-library-new-request-org.glassfish.jersey.core-jersey-server-3.0.8-a387d1d5\n\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test authoring/verification rather than pure coverage. Metrics reached 21/30 dynamic-access coverage (70.00%), but after 8 iterations the run still reported Generated LOC = 0 and ended on the same commit it started from (`37a5d9f89f3ed43ba580cea982a65a2ff089d9d9`). In `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T19-28-03-412049Z.log`, the generated `VfsSchemeResourceFinderFactoryInnerVfsResourceFinderTest` failed with `NoClassDefFoundError: org/jboss/logging/BasicLogger` while calling `org.jboss.vfs.VFS.mountReal(...)`. A later verification run in `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T19-28-38-448262Z.log` still failed in generated Jersey tests (`ArrayExtractorTest`, `ClassWriterTest`, `VfsSchemeResourceFinderFactoryInnerVfsResourceFinderTest`) with Jersey startup/native issues including `ModelValidationException`, `NoSuchMethodException` for `org.glassfish.jersey.internal.inject.ParamConverters$AggregatedProvider`, and `Invalid logger interface org.jboss.vfs.VFSLogger`.\n\nThe metadata loop also did not converge. `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-06T19-29-51-352393Z.log` failed because `native-image-agent` could not be loaded (`libnative-image-agent.so` missing), and `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-06T19-29-53-769931Z.log` still reported missing registrations such as `org.osgi.framework.BundleReference`. The broader iterative trace is in `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8/metadata-fix/codex.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Recreate or finish the Jersey-specific tests from the preserved branch and make the test project self-contained, especially the JBoss VFS runtime dependency path (`jboss-vfs` plus `jboss-logging`).\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish.jersey.core:jersey-server:3.0.8`, then fix the remaining native-image metadata surfaced by `nativeTest` / `runNativeTraceImage` for Jersey startup, WADL/JAXB, and provider reflection.\n3. Run `generateMetadata` again in an environment with a working `native-image-agent`, or collect the remaining registrations manually if that agent setup is still unavailable."}}
